# Core Workflow

Authoritative source of repo-wide facts. Scoped rules may refine, never contradict.

## Stack

- Shopify Hydrogen storefront on Remix, deployed to Shopify Oxygen (Cloudflare Workers).
- React 18 + TypeScript, Vite 5 build, Tailwind CSS + DaisyUI styling.
- GraphQL via Shopify Storefront API with Hydrogen codegen.
- Tests: Vitest (unit) + Playwright (E2E).

## Toolchain

- Node `>=18.19`, Yarn `4.5.3` (Corepack-managed).
- TypeScript path alias: `~/*` maps to `app/*`.
- ESLint + Prettier; do not fight formatter output.

## Commands

- `yarn dev` / `yarn preview` / `yarn build`
- `yarn codegen` after any GraphQL change
- `yarn typecheck` / `yarn lint` / `yarn format`
- `yarn test` / `yarn test:e2e`
- `yarn shopify:sync:*` / `yarn shopify:store-sync:*` for catalog and store mirroring

## Environment

Required at runtime:

- `SESSION_SECRET`
- `PUBLIC_STOREFRONT_API_TOKEN`
- `PRIVATE_STOREFRONT_API_TOKEN`
- `PUBLIC_STORE_DOMAIN`
- `PUBLIC_STOREFRONT_ID`

Optional: `PUBLIC_STOREFRONT_API_VERSION` (defaults to `2025-04`), `KLAVIYO_*`, `SHOPIFY_CLIENT_ID`/`SHOPIFY_CLIENT_SECRET` (admin sync scripts).

When adding a new env var, update `.env.example`, `env.d.ts`, and `README.md` together.

## Working Principles

- Prefer existing patterns; do not introduce new architecture without cause.
- Preserve Cloudflare Workers compatibility in all server code (no Node-only APIs).
- Keep changes small, typed, and consistent with neighboring code.
- Treat `lfs -> /mnt/e/lfs` as optional local asset storage; never rely on it for app runtime.

## Avoid

- Changing Node/Yarn/TS/Vite versions opportunistically.
- Committing secrets or populated `.env` files.
- Duplicating conventions across rule files; route and cache specifics live in their scoped rules.
